title: Death of Carrickmines fire victims unbelievable and heartbreaking funeral hears
text:
Death of Carrickmines fire victims 'unbelievable and heartbreaking', funeral hears 
Irish Examiner Friday 23rd October, 2015 
It was a sombre day in Wexford today as the funerals of the Carrickmines victims took place at the Church of The Assumption on Bride Street.Hundreds of mourners turned up to pay their respects to the family of Thomas and Syliva Connors who were laid to rest today along with their three children Jim, aged five, Christy, aged two and Mary, aged just five months.Taoiseach Enda Kenny was in attendance at the ceremony....
